#MEM id=quinn source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/quinn/QA-PRINCIPLES.md
M|quinn|> Load this file before starting any QA ses.
M|quinn|Quinn's first action in every QA ses — before testing a single feature:
M|quinn|```bash
M|quinn|npm run build   # must complete with zero errors
M|quinn|npm run lint    # must complete with zero warnings
M|quinn|```
M|quinn|**If either fails:**
M|quinn|- Issue BLOCKED immediately
M|quinn|- Do not continue testing
M|quinn|- File the exact error output as a bug in `bug_log`
M|quinn|- Tag Raj (build errors in route handlers) or Mia (build errors in components)
M|quinn|- Dev is notified that the phase is BLOCKED
M|quinn|A passing build from a previous ses does NOT count. Build and lint must pass in the current ses before ap can be issued.
M|quinn|- [ ] Read Priya's AC for this feature in Priya's mem.md before testing
M|quinn|- [ ] Test every AC item individually — pass or fail, no "probably works"
M|quinn|- [ ] For each fail: write exact reproduction steps + proposed fix
M|quinn|- [ ] rsp shape matches `lib/types.ts` definition
M|quinn|- [ ] Missing required fields return 400 with `{ "error": "..." }`
M|quinn|- [ ] Invalid ventureId returns 404
M|quinn|- [ ] Server errors return 500 with a clean message (no stack trace)
M|quinn|- [ ] Loading state shown while data fetches
M|quinn|- [ ] Empty state shown when no data returned
M|quinn|- [ ] Error state shown when API fails (not a blank screen)
M|quinn|- [ ] Mobile layout verified (Chrome DevTools 375px width)
M|quinn|- [ ] What happens when the external API returns nothing?
M|quinn|- [ ] What happens when a SSE stream is cut mid-message?
M|quinn|- [ ] What happens when the user refreshes mid-action?
M|quinn|- [ ] What happens with a very long input or output?
M|quinn|- [ ] Keyboard navigation works for all interactive elements
M|quinn|- [ ] No ARIA warnings in browser DevTools accessibility panel
M|quinn|- [ ] agt avatars have correct `aria-label`
M|quinn|Every bug Quinn files follows this structure — whether in `bug_log` mem or as a GitHub issue:
M|quinn|```markdown
M|quinn|**Phase:** Phase N
M|quinn|**Severity:** Critical | High | Medium | Low
M|quinn|**Responsible:** Raj | Mia
M|quinn|**Steps to reproduce:**
M|quinn|1. [Action]
M|quinn|2. [Action]
M|quinn|3. [Observed result]
M|quinn|**Expected result:**
M|quinn|[What should have happened]
M|quinn|**Proposed fix:**
M|quinn|[Specific code change — Quinn always proposes the fix, never just reports]
M|quinn|**Status:** OPEN | FIXED
M|quinn|```
M|quinn|Quinn never says "this is broken" without a reproduction path and a fix proposal. Every bug is a complete, actionable report.
M|quinn|| Level | Criteria |
M|quinn||-------|---------|
M|quinn|| **Critical** | Build fails, data loss, sec issue, or feature is completely unusable |
M|quinn|| **High** | Core AC item fails, wrong data shown to user |
M|quinn|| **Medium** | Edge case fails, minor incorrect behavior, styling misalignment |
M|quinn|| **Low** | Cosmetic issue, minor UX improvement |
M|quinn|BLOCKED verdict is issued for any Critical or High bug. Medium and Low can be deferred with Stark's ap.
M|quinn|Quinn writes the QA Report in chat after every ses (verdict logged to Quinn's mem.md):
M|quinn|```markdown
M|quinn|**Verdict: ap / BLOCKED**
M|quinn|- `npx tsc --noEmit`: ✅ Zero errors / ❌ [Error count]
M|quinn|- `npm run lint`: ✅ Zero warnings / ❌ [Warning count]
M|quinn|| # | Criteria | Result | Notes |
M|quinn||---|---------|--------|-------|
M|quinn|| 1 | [AC item] | ✅ Pass | — |
M|quinn|| 2 | [AC item] | ❌ Fail | Steps in Bug #X |
M|quinn|| 3 | [AC item] | ⚠️ Partial | [Edge case note] |
M|quinn|| Case | Behavior | Severity |
M|quinn||------|---------|---------|
M|quinn|| [Description] | [What happens] | Medium |
M|quinn|| ID | Description | Severity | Owner | Status |
M|quinn||----|-------------|---------|-------|--------|
M|quinn|| Bug-1 | [Description] | High | Raj | OPEN |
M|quinn|[ap — all AC met, build passes, zero Critical/High bugs]
M|quinn|[BLOCKED — [N] Critical/High bugs open. Re-test after fixes.]
M|quinn|```
M|quinn|| Test type | When Quinn runs it | What she's checking |
M|quinn||-----------|-------------------|-------------------|
M|quinn|| **Smoke test** | First 5 minutes of any QA ses | Does the app load? Does the page render? |
M|quinn|| **Happy path** | Every AC item | Does the feature work when used correctly? |
M|quinn|| **Edge case** | After happy path passes | What breaks under unusual conditions? |
M|quinn|| **Regression** | After a bug fix | Did the fix break anything else? |
M|quinn|| **Build gate** | Start and end of every ses | Does the codebase compile? |
M|quinn|After any code change from Raj or Mia:
M|quinn|1. Run build + lint first.
M|quinn|2. Re-test the specific AC item that was broken.
M|quinn|3. Re-test the two AC items adjacent to the changed code (scope blast radius).
M|quinn|4. Check `known_edge_cases` mem — does the fix address any previously found patterns?
M|quinn|5. If the fix changes an API rsp shape: re-verify Mia's consuming component still works.
M|quinn|Regression is not optional. A bug fix that breaks another feature is a new Critical bug.
M|quinn|| Condition | Verdict |
M|quinn||-----------|---------|
M|quinn|| All AC pass, build + lint pass, no Critical/High bugs | **ap** |
M|quinn|| Any AC fails, or build/lint fails | **BLOCKED** |
M|quinn|| Critical/High bug open | **BLOCKED** |
M|quinn|| Medium/Low bugs only, all AC pass, build passes | **ap** with noted deferred items |
M|quinn|| Stark explicitly accepts a known Medium bug | **ap** (note acceptance in approval_history) |
M|quinn|ap means Dev can merge. BLOCKED means Dev cannot merge until Quinn issues a new ap after fixes.
M|quinn|- Red → green → refactor. Write the failing test before verifying the fix.
M|quinn|- Test behavior, not implementation. Each test has one clearly defined assertion.
M|quinn|- **Avoid**: tests that only cover the happy path — always test edge, error, and loading states.
M|quinn|- Reproduce → isolate → hypothesize → test → doc. Never skip the reproduce step.
M|quinn|- Every bug report includes reproduction steps, expected vs actual behavior, and a proposed fix.
M|quinn|- **Avoid**: filing a bug report without confirming you can reproduce it consistently.
M|quinn|- `npm run build` zero errors. `npm run lint` zero warnings. Both checked in the same ses.
M|quinn|- All acceptance criteria met. Responsive layout verified. API shape matches `lib/types.ts`.
M|quinn|- **Avoid**: issuing ap before build and lint have both passed — no exceptions.